archetypes.name: Limits to Success
archetypes.rationale: The model shows growth in Core Developers and knowledge transfer, but Developer Turnover creates a balancing loop that limits sustained growth, representing a classic limits to success pattern where reinforcing growth hits a constraint.

variables.name: Community Attractiveness
variables.description: Overall appeal of the community to retain developers
variables.rationale: Needed to represent the balancing feedback from turnover that limits growth

variables.name: Workload Pressure
variables.description: Pressure on existing developers from increased community size
variables.rationale: Missing variable that could drive turnover and create the limiting constraint

connections.rationale: More developers create coordination overhead and workload
Increased pressure leads to higher turnover

archetypes.name: Shifting the Burden
archetypes.rationale: The model shows reliance on Explicit Knowledge Transfer (documentation) as a symptomatic solution, potentially shifting burden away from more fundamental Implicit Knowledge Transfer (mentorship) which builds stronger community capabilities.

variables.name: Mentorship Capacity
variables.rationale: Missing fundamental capacity variable for implicit knowledge transfer

variables.name: Documentation Dependency
variables.description: Degree of reliance on documentation over mentorship
variables.rationale: Represents the symptomatic solution that weakens fundamental capabilities

connections.rationale: More documentation increases dependency on this approach
Documentation dependency reduces investment in mentorship

archetypes.name: Growth and Underinvestment
archetypes.rationale: The model shows knowledge transfer and community growth but lacks explicit investment in capacity building (mentorship, documentation infrastructure) that could lead to degradation as community scales.

variables.name: Knowledge Infrastructure Investment
variables.description: Resources allocated to building knowledge transfer capabilities
variables.rationale: Missing investment variable that prevents underinvestment

variables.name: Perceived Performance Gap
variables.description: Difference between desired and actual knowledge transfer effectiveness

connections.rationale: High turnover indicates knowledge transfer problems
